# LYNQ UI Documentation

This document provides a detailed breakdown of the current User Interface (UI) for the LYNQ project, describing the layout and specific components found on each screen.

## Shared Components
These components appear across multiple screens.

### 1. Sidebar (Left Navigation)
The sidebar is collapsible and contains:
*   **Header**:
    *   **Logo**: Bolt icon.
    *   **Close Button**: X icon.
*   **Navigation Menu**:
    *   **New Chat**: Button to reset/start a new chat.
    *   **Search Chats**: Button to toggle search input.
    *   **Library**: Link to the Tools screen.
    *   **Projects**: Link to the Projects screen.
    *   **"Your chats" Label**: Divider.
    *   **Chat Search Input**: Hidden by default, appears on toggle.
    *   **Recent Chats List**: Dynamic list of chat history (scrollable).
*   **Footer**:
    *   **User Profile Button**: Avatar, Name, Plan badge. Toggles the Profile Popup Menu.
    *   **Upgrade Button**: Triggers Pricing Modal.
*   **Profile Popup Menu** (Appears on click):
    *   Edit Profile (Navigates to Profile screen)
    *   Upgrade Plan
    *   Personalization / Settings (Navigates to Settings screen)
    *   Help (Navigates to Help screen)
    *   Logout Button

### 2. Top Bar (Header)
The top navigation bar contains:
*   **Left Section**:
    *   **Sidebar Toggle**: Bolt + Sidebar icon composite button.
    *   **Tier Selector**: Dropdown to switch between "LYNQ" (Free) and "LYNQ Pro" (Upgrade).
*   **Right Section**:
    *   **New Chat Button**: Visible on non-home pages (or mobile), navigates to the Home screen.
    *   **Auth Buttons** (If logged out): "Login" and "Sign Up".
    *   **Profile Avatar** (If logged in): Shows user initial/image. Clicking opens the **Header Profile Dropdown** (Change Avatar, Edit Profile, Settings, Logout).

### 3. Modals & Overlays
*   **Pricing Modal**: Comparison of Starter (Free), Pro ($19/mo), and Team ($49/mo) plans.
*   **Profile Popup Overlay**: Central modal showing large avatar, name, email, plan badge, and logout.
*   **Toast Notification**: Floating notification for success/error messages.

